==English==

====Alternative spellings====
*(''US'') [[airplane]]

===Etymology===
From Greek ''[[aero-]]'', air + ''[[πλάνης]]'' planis, a wanderer

===Pronunciation===
* [[Wiktionary:Pronunciation_key|IPA]]: /ˈeərəˌpleɪn/ (plural /ˈeərəˌpleɪnz/)
* {{audio|en-uk-aeroplane.ogg|Audio (UK)}}

===Noun===
'''aeroplane''' (plural '''aeroplanes''')
# {{UK}} [[airplane]], a [[powered]] [[heavier-than-air]] [[aircraft]] with fixed [[wing]]s that obtains lift by the [[Bernoulli effect]] and is used for [[transportation]] of humans and goods; for [[amusement]] or [[entertainment]]; and in [[warfare]]; a [[plane]].

====Derived terms====
* [[plane]]

